    <!-- PermissionsActivity MIUI instruction section -->
    <string name="perm_instruction_title">Additional Device Setup</string>
    <string name="perm_instruction_disclaimer">The following instructions are relevant for modern devices running MIUI/HyperOS. Steps may differ depending on your device manufacturer.</string>
    <string name="perm_instruction_1_title">1. Disable battery restrictions</string>
    <string name="perm_instruction_1_body">Go to Settings → Apps → Kind Eye → Power → No restrictions. This prevents the system from closing the app when it thinks the app is not being actively used.</string>
    <string name="perm_instruction_2_title">2. Enable background autostart</string>
    <string name="perm_instruction_2_body">Go to Settings → Apps → Background autostart → Kind Eye. This allows the system to automatically restart the app if it was closed.</string>
    <string name="perm_instruction_3_title">3. Lock the app in Recents</string>
    <string name="perm_instruction_3_body">After launching Kind Eye, open Recent Apps, long-press the Kind Eye window, then tap the lock icon. This prevents the app from being removed from memory during a manual memory cleanup.</string>

    <string name="perm_instruction_4_title">4. Disable "Pause app activity if unused"</string>
    <string name="perm_instruction_4_body">Go to Settings → Apps → Kind Eye → Disable the toggle "Pause app activity if unused". This prevents the system from hibernating the app when it considers it idle.</string>

    <!-- General disclaimer at bottom of PermissionsActivity -->
    <string name="perm_general_disclaimer_title">Important Notice</string>
    <string name="perm_general_disclaimer_body">It is not possible to completely prevent bypassing distance monitoring if the child has sufficient technical skills. Android includes a built-in privacy and security mechanism that cannot be circumvented through standard programming means. Parents remain responsible for their children\'s health and screen usage habits.</string>

